{"type":"message","id":"42beb53e","parentId":"830edde5","timestamp":"2026-05-20T02:34:18.068Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So `channels.feishu.capabilities` is an array of strings. Let me check what the current value is - it seems like it wasn't returned in the config.get output (or was empty). Let me check the full feishu config to see what capabilities are set.\n\nAlso, looking at the HEARTBEAT.md, it says:\n```\n- Inline buttons not enabled for feishu. If you need them, ask to set feishu.capabilities.inlineButtons (\"dm\"|\"group\"|\"all\"|\"allowlist\").\n- Feishu supports interactive cards for rich messages.\n- Feishu reactions use UPPERCASE emoji type names\n```\n\nSo capabilities is used to enable features. For voice, maybe there's a capability like `voice` or `audio`? Let me check if there's documentation on what capabilities are available.\n\nActually, looking at the config output, I don't see `capabilities` listed in the feishu config section. Let me check what the actual capabilities setting is.\n\nLet me also think about the speed issue. The user says it's slower. The lossless-claw is active. Let me think about what could be slow:\n\n1. Lossless-claw does compaction - this adds overhead\n2. The model itself (MiniMax M2) - not much I can do\n3. Websocket vs webhook - websocket should be fine\n4. The feishu plugin duplication warning\n\nFor voice, the user might need to set `channels.feishu.capabilities` to include something like `audio` or `voice` if that's a supported capability. But without knowing exactly what capability string is needed, I can't be sure.\n\nLet me check if there's more info about capabilities in the docs.","thinkingSignature":"5ef788d8f2df65ae395b4ab0f58422b8a2928e17c7a2e2925b5b3aa6d3bf7b8f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_58d39w9fsaz9_1","name":"gateway","arguments":{"action":"config.schema.lookup","path":"channels.feishu"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"