{"type":"message","id":"0c7cc1ed","parentId":"4afd04d0","timestamp":"2026-05-20T02:34:49.767Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_5ivbb0pr7fud_2","toolName":"gateway","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"result\": {\n    \"path\": \"tools.media\",\n    \"schema\": {\n      \"type\": \"object\",\n      \"additionalProperties\": false\n    },\n    \"children\": [\n      {\n        \"key\": \"models\",\n        \"path\": \"tools.media.models\",\n        \"type\": \"array\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": true,\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Media Understanding Shared Models\",\n          \"help\": \"Shared fallback model list used by media understanding tools when modality-specific model lists are not set. Keep this aligned with available multimodal providers to avoid runtime fallback churn.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"models\",\n            \"media\",\n            \"tools\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"tools.media.models\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"concurrency\",\n        \"path\": \"tools.media.concurrency\",\n        \"type\": \"integer\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": false,\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Media Understanding Concurrency\",\n          \"help\": \"Maximum number of concurrent media understanding operations per turn across image, audio, and video tasks. Lower this in resource-constrained deployments to prevent CPU/network saturation.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"performance\",\n            \"media\",\n            \"tools\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"tools.media.concurrency\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"asyncCompletion\",\n        \"path\": \"tools.media.asyncCompletion\",\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": true\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"image\",\n        \"path\": \"tools.media.image\",\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": true\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"audio\",\n        \"path\": \"tools.media.audio\",\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": true\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"video\",\n        \"path\": \"tools.media.video\",\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": true\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}"}],"details":{"ok":true,"result":{"path":"tools.media","schema":{"type":"object","additionalProperties":false},"children":[{"key":"models","path":"tools.media.models","type":"array","required":false,"hasChildren":true,"hint":{"label":"Media Understanding Shared Models","help":"Shared fallback model list used by media understanding tools when modality-specific model lists are not set. Keep this aligned with available multimodal providers to avoid runtime fallback churn.","tags":["models","media","tools"]},"hintPath":"tools.media.models"},{"key":"concurrency","path":"tools.media.concurrency","type":"integer","required":false,"hasChildren":false,"hint":{"label":"Media Understanding Concurrency","help":"Maximum number of concurrent media understanding operations per turn across image, audio, and video tasks. Lower this in resource-constrained deployments to prevent CPU/network saturation.","tags":["performance","media","tools"]},"hintPath":"tools.media.concurrency"},{"key":"asyncCompletion","path":"tools.media.asyncCompletion","type":"object","required":false,"hasChildren":true},{"key":"image","path":"tools.media.image","type":"object","required":false,"hasChildren":true},{"key":"audio","path":"tools.media.audio","type":"object","required":false,"hasChildren":true},{"key":"video","path":"tools.media.video","type":"object","required":false,"hasChildren":true}]}},"isError":false,"timestamp":1779244489682}}
{"type":"message","id":"8df043fc","parentId":"0c7cc1ed","timestamp":"2026-05-20T02:34:57.299Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So:\n1. **ffmpeg is NOT installed** (command exited with code 1) - this means voice message transcoding won't work properly\n2. `tools.media.audio` exists but I need to see what config it needs\n\nLet me check the tools.media.audio schema and also check if there's anything in the current config about media/audio.","thinkingSignature":"0546ebcca9e97e1f0f7666954d05d15d78448d7e04d81ee32f0abefd41d9113f"},{"type":"text","text":"**问题发现了：**\n\n1. **ffmpeg 未安装** — 语音消息需要 ffmpeg 转码\n2. 需要检查 `tools.media.audio` 配置\n\n让我继续检查：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_43z6tmth79ci_1","name":"gateway","arguments":{"action":"config.schema.lookup","path":"tools.media.audio"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_43z6tmth79ci_2","name":"gateway","arguments":{"action":"config.get","path":"tools"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":11344,"output":179,"cacheRead":43702,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":55225,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779244489769,"responseId":"065c50cac9de77e7308d310e8c9e5554"}}
{"type":"message","id":"013190bd","parentId":"8df043fc","timestamp":"2026-05-20T02:34:57.979Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_43z6tmth79ci_1","toolName":"gateway","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"result\": {\n    \"path\": \"tools.media.audio\",\n    \"schema\": {\n      \"type\": \"object\",\n      \"additionalProperties\": false\n    },\n    \"children\": [\n      {\n        \"key\": \"enabled\",\n        \"path\": \"tools.media.audio.enabled\",\n        \"type\": \"boolean\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": false,\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Enable Audio Understanding\",\n          \"help\": \"Enable audio understanding so voice notes or audio clips can be transcribed/summarized for agent context. Disable when audio ingestion is outside policy or unnecessary for your workflows.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"media\",\n            \"tools\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"tools.media.audio.enabled\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"scope\",\n        \"path\": \"tools.media.audio.scope\",\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": true,\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Audio Understanding Scope\",\n          \"help\": \"Scope selector for when audio understanding runs across inbound messages and attachments. Keep focused scopes in high-volume channels to reduce cost and avoid accidental transcription.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"media\",\n            \"tools\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"tools.media.audio.scope\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"maxBytes\",\n        \"path\": \"tools.media.audio.maxBytes\",\n        \"type\": \"integer\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": false,\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Audio Understanding Max Bytes\",\n          \"help\": \"Maximum accepted audio payload size in bytes 