{"type":"message","id":"b9db7f86","parentId":"8c49ab25","timestamp":"2026-05-20T02:38:57.616Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking two questions:\n1. Is installing FFmpeg enough to make voice work?\n2. For the audio understanding feature, does it need LLM support or is it purely local?\n\nLet me answer clearly:\n\n1. For **sending** voice (TTS): FFmpeg is needed to transcode audio formats. Installing FFmpeg should be sufficient for the sending side.\n\n2. For **audio understanding** (speech-to-text/transcription): \n   - This needs a transcription provider - either a cloud service (like Deepgram, Whisper API, or built into some LLM providers) or a local model (like Whisper local)\n   - It's not purely local unless you run a local Whisper model\n   - The `tools.media.audio` config needs a provider\n\nActually, looking at the earlier doc more carefully:\n> When `tools.media.audio` is configured, OpenClaw downloads the voice-note resource and runs shared audio transcription before the agent turn, so the agent receives the spoken transcript.\n\nSo audio understanding requires:\n- `tools.media.audio.enabled: true`\n- A transcription provider (like deepgram, or could use some LLM providers that support audio input)\n\nThe audio understanding is about receiving voice notes and transcribing them so the agent can understand what was said. This is different from sending voice (TTS).\n\nLet me provide a clear answer:\n\n1. Sending voice: Install FFmpeg, then `asVoice` should work\n2. Receiving/transcribing voice: Needs `tools.media.audio` config + a transcription provider (cloud or local Whisper)\n\nI should explain that audio understanding typically needs either:\n- A cloud transcription service (Deepgram, etc.)\n- A local Whisper model\n\nNeither is purely \"local\" in the sense of no external service, unless you set up a local Whisper server.\n","thinkingSignature":"28da7990e302326f393b88b1704e744278237b27c796ad7f27585c748e8123c4"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n确认一下两个问题的答案：\n\n---\n\n## 1. 安装 FFmpeg 就能发语音？\n\n**基本正确。** FFmpeg 负责把音频转成飞书需要的 Ogg/Opus 格式。\n\n安装命令：\n```bash\nsudo apt install ffmpeg\n```\n\n装完重启 gateway 就行，`asVoice` 就能正常发送语音消息了。\n\n---\n\n## 2. audio.Understanding 是需要大模型还是纯本地？\n\n**需要转录服务，不是纯本地。** 具体分两种：\n\n**方案 A：云服务（推荐）**\n- Deepgram、Gladia、Fireflies 等\n- 配置好 API Key 就行，延迟低，质量好\n- 示例配置：\n```json\n{\n  \"tools\": {\n    \"media\": {\n      \"audio\": {\n        \"enabled\": true,\n        \"providerOptions\": {\n          \"deepgram\": {\n            \"apiKey\": \"***\"\n          }\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**方案 B：本地 Whisper**\n- 可以跑本地的 Whisper 模型\n- 需要自己部署一个 Whisper API 服务\n- 然后配置 `baseUrl` 指向你的本地服务\n\n---\n\n## 总结\n\n| 功能 | 依赖 |\n|------|------|\n| **发语音**（文字转语音） | FFmpeg ✅ 本地就能搞定 |\n| **收语音**（语音转文字） | 需要转录服务（云 or 本地 Whisper） |\n\n你想先搞哪个？发语音比较简单，装完 FFmpeg 就行。收语音要看你要不要接一个转录服务。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1525,"output":703,"cacheRead":55168,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":57396,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779244697954,"responseId":"065c519ab159e5d5eb125689b567724e"}}
