{"type":"message","id":"a52274e7","parentId":"07a7cf3b","timestamp":"2026-05-20T02:41:46.652Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The sender is \"LeiChao\" sending \"中心测试。\" - This seems like another communication test from a different user (LeiChao) in what appears to be a WeCom (企业微信) channel, not Feishu.\n\nLooking at the inbound context at the top of the prompt, I see there's a wecom channel configuration. The conversation info shows:\n- chat_id: \"wecom:LeiChao\"\n- message_id: \"27e05fdfde9f559944cc9f84f0f63a7b\"\n- sender_id: \"LeiChao\"\n- sender: \"LeiChao\"\n\nSo this is a WeCom message from someone named LeiChao. They're doing a communication test (\"中心测试\" = \"center test\" or \"central test\").\n\nI should respond simply and directly, acknowledging the test. This is WeCom, not Feishu, so the previous conversation about Feishu voice features doesn't directly apply here.\n\nSince this is a direct message from LeiChao, I should just respond naturally.\n","thinkingSignature":"b52fe904e623b057f2a072bd3181d3d06b7e1d3620389bd3c326d3247bb3d5d4"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n收到，中心测试通信正常 🎯"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":49301,"output":227,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":49528,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779244879724,"responseId":"065c52501bf6544f118845c06b712b32"}}
