{"type":"message","id":"3aa8719b","parentId":"b91dfe79","timestamp":"2026-05-20T02:59:11.245Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The API endpoint doesn't exist or requires authentication. Let me try a different approach - maybe check if there are any openclaw CLI commands that show channel status.\n\nActually, let me re-read the logs I already have and think about what the issue might be. The user is saying both WeChat and WeCom are not working despite showing as \"enabled\" in the backend.\n\nLooking at the logs again:\n1. WeChat plugin is loaded and compatible\n2. WeCom plugin needs a restart due to config changes\n3. There's no indication of any inbound messages being received by either channel\n\nThe issue could be:\n1. For WeChat: The QR login might have worked but the session might not be active. The plugin might need a proper login to receive messages.\n2. For WeCom: The plugin was updated but needs a restart to load the new version.\n\nAlso, looking at the earlier warning about WeCom: \"config change requires gateway restart\" - this means the WeCom plugin was updated and the current gateway process is running the old version. The new version will only take effect after a full restart.\n\nBut I already triggered a restart earlier. Let me check if it actually restarted or if it deferred due to active operations.\n\nLooking at the logs:\n- The restart was deferred multiple times due to active replies\n- Eventually there was a shutdown at `2026-05-20T02:55:53.427Z warn gateway/shutdown {\"subsystem\":\"gateway/shutdown\"} restart reply drain timed out after 300001ms with 3 pending reply(ies) still active; continuing shutdown`\n\nSo the gateway did shut down and should have restarted. But the wecom plugin config change warning suggests that after the restart, the new wecom plugin config was detected but needs another restart.\n\nActually wait - looking at the logs more carefully:\n- The warning about wecom plugin needing restart appeared BEFORE the actual restart\n- Then after the restart, I see new log entries with timestamps after `2026-05-20T02:56:02.260Z`\n\n\n- The gateway is running now (new PID 374503)\n\nSo the restart did happen. The issue might be that even after restarting, the WeCom plugin still shows as needing a restart because the config change was detected but not fully applied. This could indicate a deeper problem with the WeCom plugin - either it wasn't fully installed correctly, there's a configuration error, or it can't establish a connection to WeCom's servers. I should look more carefully at the WeCom configuration and see if there are any connection issues or misconfigurations preventing it from working properly.","thinkingSignature":"886f4a7673385ee7aac46cbb13d5982882f421f2954cc18ea4ec3bf41802bfed"},{"type":"text","text":"Let me check the full log output to see if there's more information about WeCom or WeChat issues:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ipjr9cuv9akn_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw logs 2>&1 | grep -i -E \"(error|warn|fail|disconnect|connect|channel)\" | tail -40"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":27413,"output":609,"cacheRead":45375,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":73397,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779245932437,"responseId":"065c566c85294ac7811f0288a1489fd2"}}
