{"type":"message","id":"5a65dba4","parentId":"ca0e24d1","timestamp":"2026-05-20T02:59:38.236Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Looking at the logs, I can see:\n\n1. **WeChat (openclaw-weixin)**: \n   - Shows `[compat] Host OpenClaw 2026.5.18 >= 2026.3.22, OK.` - this means the plugin is compatible and loaded\n   - But I don't see any actual connection status or \"connected\" message for WeChat\n   - The plugin is loaded but I don't see any indication that it's actually connected and receiving messages\n\n2. **WeCom (wecom-openclaw-plugin)**:\n   - Shows `config change requires gateway restart` for the wecom plugin\n   - This suggests the plugin was updated but needs a restart to take effect\n   - But there's no actual \"connected\" or \"error\" message for WeCom either\n\n3. There's also an error: `secrets.resolve failed: Secrets runtime snapshot is not active.` - this might be related to some configuration issue.\n\nThe key issue is that I don't see any actual connection success or failure messages for either channel. The logs only show:\n- The plugin is compatible/loaded\n- Config warnings about feishu being duplicated\n- Auth profile warnings about invalid entries\n\nBut no actual \"connected to WeChat\" or \"connected to WeCom\" messages, and no errors about failed connections either.\n\nThis is strange. Let me think about what the user means by \"not working\":\n- They set up WeChat via QR code\n- They set up WeCom (configured with botId and secret)\n- But messages aren't getting replies\n\nFor WeCom, looking at the channels config earlier:\n```json\n\"wecom\": {\n    \"enabled\": true,\n    \"botId\": \"aib4H1edblYf-DEub6oxTN2s-B4WLkE5PDc\",\n    \"secret\": \"JfFd6m…AUhi\"\n\n\n}\n```\n\nThis is in the channels section. But the wecom-openclaw-plugin is also in the plugins section with `enabled: true`. So there might be two different things:\n1. The built-in wecom channel (if any)\n2. The wecom-openclaw-plugin\n\nLooking at the plugins list earlier:\n- `wecom-openclaw-plugin: { enabled: true }`\n\nSo the wecom plugin is enabled. But is it actually configured to use the channel properly? The channel config says `wecom: { enabled: true, botId: ..., secret: ... }` but the plugin might need its own configuration to connect properly.\n\nI'm not seeing clear connection success or failure messages for either channel in the logs. The WeChat plugin shows compatibility but no actual connection status, and WeCom shows a config change requiring restart but no connection confirmation either. There's also that secrets resolution error which could indicate a configuration problem. The issue might be that the plugins are enabled but not properly configured to actually connect to their respective services. The WeCom plugin appears to be a separate installation from the npm packages rather than a built-in component. To properly diagnose the issue, I should restart the gateway again since the wecom-openclaw-plugin is showing a config change that requires a restart, and this restart was deferred earlier. After restarting, I can check the logs to see if both WeChat and WeCom show proper connection status. The user mentioned both are enabled in the backend, so once restarted, I should verify they're actually connected and receiving messages properly.","thinkingSignature":"fadb7d4c08899508f2a57457da791a10096115d87bb115e3762c015a681d3cd9"},{"type":"text","text":"根据日志分析，我发现了问题：\n\n**问题分析：**\n\n1. **企业微信 (WeCom)**：`wecom-openclaw-plugin` 显示 `config change requires gateway restart` — 插件有更新但还未完全生效\n\n2. **个人微信 (WeChat)**：插件已加载（`openclaw-weixin [compat] OK`），但没有看到连接成功的日志\n\n日志里没有看到任何 WeChat 或 WeCom **实际连接成功**的明确信息。\n\n让我再重启一次 gateway，确保所有插件都正确加载：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fow186lgetor_1","name":"gateway","arguments":{"action":"restart","note":"再次重启网关，确保微信和企业微信插件完全加载"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":30097,"output":873,"cacheRead":45375,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":76345,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779245954583,"responseId":"065c56836bb36c89a55142700029730d"}}
{"type":"message","id":"81b7784f","parentId":"5a65dba4","timestamp":"2026-05-20T02:59:38.420Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_fow186lgetor_1","toolName":"gateway","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"pid\": 374503,\n  \"signal\": \"SIGUSR1\",\n  \"delayMs\": 2000,\n  \"mode\": \"emit\",\n  \"coalesced\": false,\n  \"cooldownMsApplied\": 0\n}"}],"details":{"ok":true,"pid":374503,"signal":"SIGUSR1","delayMs":2000,"mode":"emit","coalesced":false,"cooldownMsApplied":0},"isError":false,"timestamp":1779245978302}}
{"type":"message","id":"033e09ba","parentId":"81b7784f","timestamp":"2026-05-20T02:59:50.309Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The gateway restart was initiated. I should wait a moment and then check the logs to see if WeCom and WeChat are properly connected after the restart.\n\nActually, I should think about this more carefully. The wecom-openclaw-plugin needs a restart due to config changes. But what config changes? Looking at the warning message again:\n\n```\nconfig change requires gateway restart (plugins.installs.wecom-openclaw-plugin.spec, plugins.installs.wecom-openclaw-plugin.version, plugins.installs.wecom-openclaw-plugin.resolvedVersion, plugins.installs.wecom-openclaw-plugin.resolvedSpec, plugins.installs.wecom-openclaw-plugin.integrity, plugins.installs.wecom-openclaw-plugin.shasum)\n```\n\nThis suggests that the plugin's spec/version/integrity changed - which typically happens when the plugin is updated. But the restart was deferred multiple times and eventually the gateway did shut down and restart. So after the restart, the new plugin version should be loaded.\n\nBut the warning appeared BEFORE the restart. After the restart, the new log entries don't show the warning again, which suggests the new version was loaded successfully.\n\nLet me wait a moment and then check the logs again to see if WeCom and WeChat are properly connected.\n\nActually, I realize I should check if there's a way to see the actual channel status. Maybe there's an `openclaw channels` command or something similar.\n\nLet me also check if there's more information about the WeCom connection.","thinkingSignature":"3a5559451854c18af500030221ce71bc0d6b550bc1b06e039693cb5737803dd5"},{"type":"text","text":"重启信号已发出。稍等几秒后，让我检查一下日志确认两个插件是否都正常加载了：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rc413xgz4toe_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sleep 5 && openclaw logs 2>&1 | grep -i -E \"(wecom|weixin|wechat|微信|channel)\" | tail -30","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":31020,"output":387,"cacheRead":45375,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":76782,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779245978424,"responseId":"065c569a28df187e505f6a2e0c2acea9"}}
