{"type":"message","id":"9710ff63","parentId":"81708920","timestamp":"2026-05-20T03:01:12.229Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The logs still show the same content. There's no new WeCom or WeChat connection logs after the restart. The last entries are from around 03:00, and they don't show any new channel connection activity.\n\nLooking at the situation:\n1. WeChat was bound successfully earlier (bot already connected)\n2. But after multiple restarts, there's no new connection logs\n3. WeCom has no connection logs at all\n\nThis is concerning. The user is saying that messages to WeChat and WeCom are not getting replies.\n\nLet me think about what could be wrong:\n\n1. **WeChat**: The plugin is loaded and was connected before. But after restarts, maybe the connection is not being re-established? Or maybe there's an issue with the WeChat API connection?\n\n2. **WeCom**: The plugin is enabled but I haven't seen any logs about it trying to connect or any errors. This is suspicious.\n\nActually, wait - I see the WeChat logs show that it was binding at around 02:28-02:29. This was BEFORE the user said they \"just installed\" WeChat. So maybe:\n- The user installed WeChat and did the QR scan\n- The binding was successful\n- But then after restarts, maybe the connection dropped or wasn't properly restored\n\nFor WeCom, the situation is less clear. There's no logs showing any attempt to connect.\n\nLet me think about what the user actually sees:\n- They send a message to the WeChat bot - no reply\n- They send a message to the WeCom bot - no reply\n\nBoth channels are configured and enabled, but not working.\n\nPossible issues:\n1. The WeChat connection might have dropped and not reconnected\n2. WeCom might not be properly configured to receive messages\n3. There might be a network/firewall issue\n4. The plugins might need a full restart (not just SIGUSR1)\n\nLet me suggest to the user that we need to do a more thorough diagnosis. Maybe we should:\n1. Check the WeChat login status\n\n\n2. Verify WeCom is actually receiving messages through its webhook configuration\n3. Look at the WeCom bot's API connection status\n\nI should give the user a clear summary of what I found and what we should try next.","thinkingSignature":"05ff8a60a0c3c7676b681ad719494cd1fbce06fd6325225d3fd3f12235221d76"},{"type":"text","text":"日志没有显示微信或企业微信在重启后建立新连接的记录。这很奇怪。\n\n**现状总结：**\n\n| 渠道 | 配置状态 | 实际连接状态 |\n|------|---------|-------------|\n| **微信** | ✅ 已绑定 | ❓ 重启后无新连接日志 |\n| **企业微信** | ✅ enabled | ❌ 完全无连接日志 |\n\n**问题分析：**\n\n1. **微信** — 之前扫码绑定成功了，但重启后没有重新建立连接的日志。可能连接丢失了。\n\n2. **企业微信** — 完全没有连接日志，说明插件可能根本没有尝试连接，或者配置有问题（webhook/secret 等）。\n\n**需要你帮我确认：**\n\n1. 你往**微信**发消息时，日志里有没有出现 `openclaw-weixin` 收到消息的记录？\n2. 你往**企业微信**发消息时，是发到哪里？机器人？webhook？还是别的？\n\n另外，让我检查一下企业微信的 channel 配置是否正确：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_zavmo48s0k0o_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /home/halei/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"\nimport json,sys\nd=json.load(sys.stdin)\nwecom = d.get('channels', {}).get('wecom', {})\nprint('WeCom channel config:')\nprint(json.dumps(wecom, indent=2))\nprint()\nplugins = d.get('plugins', {}).get('entries', {}).get('wecom-openclaw-plugin', {})\nprint('WeCom plugin config:')\nprint(json.dumps(plugins, indent=2))\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":35622,"output":798,"cacheRead":45375,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":81795,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779246048092,"responseId":"065c56e04d180cf3fc2a8f2d35b7ade8"}}
{"type":"message","id":"03e1c228","parentId":"9710ff63","timestamp":"2026-05-20T03:01:12.477Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_zavmo48s0k0o_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"WeCom channel config:\n{\n  \"enabled\": true,\n  \"botId\": \"aib4H1edblYf-DEub6oxTN2s-B4WLkE5PDc\",\n  \"secret\": \"JfFd6m…AUhi\"\n}\n\nWeCom plugin config:\n{\n  \"enabled\": true\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":47,"aggregated":"WeCom channel config:\n{\n  \"enabled\": true,\n  \"botId\": \"aib4H1edblYf-DEub6oxTN2s-B4WLkE5PDc\",\n  \"secret\": \"***\"\n}\n\nWeCom plugin config:\n{\n  \"enabled\": true\n}","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1779246072328}}
{"type":"message","id":"8081c79e","parentId":"03e1c228","timestamp":"2026-05-20T03:01:37.866Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the WeCom config. The channel config has `botId` and `secret`, and the plugin is enabled. But there's no additional configuration like webhook URL or connection mode. This might be the issue - maybe the WeCom plugin needs more configuration to actually connect.\n\nLooking at the WeCom configuration, it seems very basic. It just has botId and secret. But how does it connect? WeCom typically uses webhook mode for receiving messages (not WebSocket like Feishu).\n\nLooking at the earlier Feishu config:\n- `connectionMode: \"websocket\"`\n\nBut for WeCom, I don't see a connectionMode. Maybe WeCom uses webhook by default? If so, it needs a webhook URL configured on the WeCom Open Platform side, and OpenClaw needs to be accessible from the internet to receive webhook events.\n\nWait - looking at the gateway status:\n- Gateway is bound to loopback only: `bind=loopback (127.0.0.1)`\n- Dashboard: `http://127.0.0.1:18789/`\n\nThis means the gateway is only accessible locally! If WeCom tries to reach the gateway via webhook, it wouldn't be able to because the gateway is on loopback only.\n\nBut wait - looking at the Feishu config, it uses WebSocket mode, which means Feishu connects OUT to OpenClaw, not the other way around. So Feishu works even with loopback because OpenClaw initiates the connection to Feishu.\n\nFor WeCom, if it uses webhook mode, WeCom would need to send messages TO OpenClaw, which wouldn't work if OpenClaw is on loopback only.\n\nBut actually, I don't see any webhook configuration for WeCom either. Let me check if the wecom-openclaw-plugin has its own connection mechanism.\n\nActually, looking at the wecom plugin name: `wecom-openclaw-plugin` - this is an external plugin. \n\nThe WeCom plugin might handle its own connection independently - perhaps it uses WeCom's SDK to maintain a persistent connection to their servers rather than relying on OpenClaw's gateway. Without seeing actual connection attempt logs though, it's hard to know if it's even trying to connect. The user should send a test message to WeCom and see if anything appears in the logs to confirm the plugin is receiving events.","thinkingSignature":"a576a00d6e26f2ab6d6e797491351519259e858c87161e5926128b70ea454461"},{"type":"text","text":"现在我看到企业微信的配置了：\n\n```json\n\"wecom\": {\n  \"enabled\": true,\n  \"botId\": \"aib4H1edblYf-DEub6oxTN2s-B4WLkE5PDc\",\n  \"secret\": \"***\"\n}\n```\n\n**问题发现：**\n\n1. **Gateway 是 loopback 模式**：`bind=loopback (127.0.0.1)` — 只监听本地\n2. 企业微信配置只有 `botId` 和 `secret`，没有看到 webhook 或者连接模式的配置\n\n**可能的原因：**\n\n- 如果企业微信用的是 **webhook 模式**（被动接收消息），那 OpenClaw 需要能从公网访问\n- Gateway 绑定在 loopback，意味着外部无法直接访问 webhook\n\n**你需要确认一下：**\n\n1. **企业微信的连接方式是什么？** 是 webhook 还是长连接？\n2. 你在企业微信后台配置的回调地址是什么？\n\n同时，你往企业微信发一条消息，然后马上看日志：\n\n```bash\nopenclaw logs --follow 2>&1 | grep -i wecom\n```\n\n发完消息后把日志发给我看看，我需要确认企业微信插件有没有收到消息。\n\n另外，**飞书是在线的**，说明 OpenClaw 本身是能正常工作的。问题可能只是微信/企业微信这两个渠道的配置问题。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":36521,"output":764,"cacheRead":45375,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":82660,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779246072480,"responseId":"065c56f894d4500409ff1f117ce82caf"}}
