{"type":"message","id":"63ba6e07","parentId":"fe6b8e90","timestamp":"2026-05-20T03:02:48.606Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is a message from \"LeiChao\" via WeCom (企业微信). The conversation info shows:\n- chat_id: \"wecom:LeiChao\"\n- message_id: \"d2f08ef0823d8ffac05a97731c75dc5b\"\n- sender_id: \"LeiChao\"\n- sender: \"LeiChao\"\n- timestamp: \"Wed 2026-05-20 11:01 GMT+8\"\n\nThis means WeCom IS working! The message came through. But I'm seeing it in the conversation with HALEI, which suggests there might be routing happening - the WeCom message from LeiChao is being routed to the current session.\n\nActually, looking at the conversation context, it seems like the message from LeiChao via WeCom was successfully received and I responded to it earlier (see the \"中心测试\" message). So WeCom is actually working!\n\nThe user earlier said \"微信呢，这个正常吗， 我都成功扫码绑定了\" and I saw in the logs that the WeChat plugin did successfully bind (log showed \"bot already bound\"). So WeChat/Weixin is working too.\n\nNow I'm receiving this message from LeiChao via WeCom, which confirms WeCom IS working.\n\nSo the answer to the user's question about why WeChat and WeCom don't work was... they actually DO work! I just successfully received and responded to a WeCom message from LeiChao.\n\nLet me respond to confirm that WeCom is working.\n","thinkingSignature":"8cf48f40d993efd7d460e8fdc97c3ac4ebf47c49c5a1a3b364e881f478e8d65e"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n收到！这条消息是从**企业微信**发过来的，说明企业微信通信正常 ✅\n\n之前你说微信和企业微信没有回复，但实际上现在这条消息就是从企业微信来的，说明通道是通的。\n\n可能之前是测试方式的问题，或者 Gateway 刚重启后恢复了。\n\n**目前状态：**\n- ✅ 企业微信（WeCom）：正常运行\n- ✅ 飞书（Feishu）：正常运行  \n- ✅ 微信（WeChat）：从日志看绑定也成功了\n\n你现在可以继续用企业微信和我说话了！🎯"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":62438,"output":419,"cacheRead":256,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":63113,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":177924612289