{"type":"message","id":"c1b337f0","parentId":"41958e82","timestamp":"2026-05-20T03:03:59.755Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user (LeiChao via WeCom) is asking if I can forward a message via WeChat (personal WeChat, not WeCom). This means they want me to send a message from WeCom to their personal WeChat account.\n\nThis is actually about cross-channel communication - they want to send a message to their personal WeChat through the WeCom bot, or vice versa.\n\nLooking at the channels:\n- WeCom (企业微信) - currently working, message came from LeiChao\n- WeChat (微信) - also configured and apparently working based on earlier logs\n\nThe user is asking: \"Can you forward a message to me via WeChat?\" This suggests they want to send something through the WeChat channel that is configured.\n\nBut wait - I don't know what message they want to forward. I should ask them what message they want to send.\n\nAlso, I need to understand the architecture here. WeCom and WeChat are two different channels. Can I send a message from WeCom to WeChat? Or are they asking me to send a message through the WeChat channel separately?\n\nLooking at the OpenClaw docs, there are multiple accounts and channel routing capabilities. But I don't know if there's a direct bridge between WeCom and WeChat messages.\n\nThe simplest interpretation is: the user wants me to send a message via WeChat (the personal WeChat channel that was configured with QR login). I need to ask them what message they want to send.\n\nLet me ask for clarification on what message they want to forward.\n","thinkingSignature":"d60943eaa2043e6395e68d29fc36525d0e6ec4f72c581a98bce15bf245411d65"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n可以！告诉我你想转发什么内容，以及发送到微信的哪里（个人微信好友/群等）。\n\n不过我需要先确认一下：你是想让我通过**企业微信**发消息，还是通过**个人微信**发？另外，接收方是谁？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":600,"output":365,"cacheRead":62528,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":63493,"cost":{"input"