{"type":"message","id":"b35ad8bc","parentId":"62c4f18a","timestamp":"2026-05-20T04:48:53.361Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Hmm, the feishu search is returning \"need_user_authorization\" error. This means the user authorization might have expired or there's a permission issue.\n\nLet me try to use the message tool to send via the current session's channel routing, or use the wecom to send a message back to confirm the cross-channel capability.\n\nActually, I should check if there's a way to send to HALEI's Feishu through the normal routing. Since I'm currently in a WeCom session with LeiChao, but HALEI is the main user on Feishu. The config has feishu configured with kiit account.\n\nActually, looking at the error - it's asking for `im:message.send_as_user` permission. This means the Feishu app doesn't have permission to send messages on behalf of users. This is a permission issue in the Feishu Open Platform.\n\nThe user said \"也用主agent发就行，kiit\" - they want me to send using the main agent (KIIT) which is connected to Feishu. But the permission error suggests the app doesn't have the right permissions.\n\nLet me try a different approach - use the message tool to send through the feishu channel directly, since I know the feishu channel is configured. But wait, the message tool sends to the current channel by default.\n\nActually, let me try sending to HALEI's Feishu directly using the feishu channel. But I need to figure out how to route from WeCom to Feishu.\n\nWait - the user is using WeCom (LeiChao), but they want to send to Feishu (HALEI). This is cross-channel. OpenClaw should be able to route between channels if properly configured.\n\nLet me try using the message tool with channel specification.\n\nActually, let me think about this differently. The user said \"用主agent发就行\" - use the main agent to send. This suggests they want me to use the KIIT agent's Feishu connection to send. But I'm already running as KIIT...\n\nThe issue is likely the Feishu app permissions. \n\nThe \"need_user_authorization\" error from feishu_search_user suggests either expired OAuth tokens or missing permissions in the Feishu Open Platform. I need to check if there are existing feishu tokens I can use, or if the user needs to reauthorize the connection. Without valid user authorization, I can't search for users or send messages on their behalf.\n","thinkingSignature":"03a98e75981405229bb0b84c2457d2e686bf8c8523d3ba4bf0bb08fd7e6e7969"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_j4myj0ynua7f_1","name":"feishu_get_user","arguments":{}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":67,"output":529,"cacheRead":64576,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65172,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779252522557,"responseId":"065c702a337fb507d7ca852694eb7585"}}
