{"type":"message","id":"018ba9a9","parentId":"d427a920","timestamp":"2026-05-20T04:49:06.643Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need user authorization to search or get user info. But the error also says \"im:message.send_as_user\" is missing - I need permission to send messages as a user.\n\nLet me check what permissions I do have. Actually, I should try using the bot message instead - feishu_im_bot_message or just use message with channel parameter.\n\nActually wait - earlier I was able to receive messages via Feishu, so the Feishu channel IS working. The issue is that I can't SEND messages as USER - I need the \"im:message.send_as_user\" permission for that.\n\nBut I CAN send messages as the BOT, not as a user. Let me check the difference...\n\nActually the user is asking me to send to Feishu. Maybe I should just try the message tool with the feishu channel. But I don't know Feishu's channel configuration - I know WeCom works.\n\nActually, let me re-read the problem: I was trying to send to HALEI's open_id as a user, but I got an error about missing permission. The permission \"im:message.send_as_user\" is needed to send messages AS A USER. I don't have that permission.\n\nBut I could try sending as the BOT instead. But the feishu_im_user_message tool description says it's \"以用户身份调用飞书用户身份IM消息工具\" - it sends AS USER. That requires permission.\n\nLet me think... I should tell the user about the permission issue. Or maybe there's another way.\n\nActually - let me check if I can just use the feishu_im_user_message but with a different approach - sending to a chat_id instead of open_id? Or maybe I should use the feishu channel directly via message tool?\n\nActually wait - I have HALEI's open_id. Maybe if I try to send a message to HALEI's Feishu, HALEI could receive it. But the error says I need \"im:message.send_as_user\" permission.\n\nThis is an OAuth/permission issue - the Feishu app needs this permission granted by the user, or I need to use a different method.\n\n\nI should let the user know about this permission gap and suggest they grant the necessary OAuth scope so I can send messages on their behalf.\n","thinkingSignature":"636dc75c7f8b05bf4215bb07ccc84a58cd78a638b496b98d4fee765dd152a129"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n遇到了权限问题。我用的是飞书用户身份（OAuth），但缺少 `im:message.send_as_user` 权限，所以不能代你发消息。\n\n**问题：** \n- 要以用户身份发消息，飞书应用需要开通 `im:message.send_as_user` 权限\n- 目前没这个权限，所以发送失败\n\n**解决方案：**\n1. 在飞书开放平台给应用开通这个权限（需要管理员操作）\n2. 或者直接通过当前的企业微信会话沟通——飞书和企业微信现在都通了，我可以通过 WeCom 回应你，不需要转发到飞书\n\n目前的状态：\n- ✅ 企业微信（WeCom）：正常\n- ✅ 飞书（Feishu）：正常（但我发消息需要额外权限）\n- ✅ 微信（WeChat）：正常\n\n你想怎么继续？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":45,"output":635,"cacheRead":64640,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65320,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779252534171,"responseId":"065c703657233aee3cf582ef8ba6a267"}}
