{"type":"message","id":"11487c53","parentId":"bd9f6f34","timestamp":"2026-05-20T06:49:27.516Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying the desktop didn't change at all. They're not seeing the browser on their end. \n\nThis is strange - I successfully opened a browser and navigated to Baidu, and took screenshots showing the browser content. But the user says nothing changed on their desktop.\n\nLet me think about why this could be happening:\n\n1. The browser opened on the server/host where OpenClaw is running, not on the user's local machine\n2. The screenshots I took were from the headless browser on the server\n3. The user expects to see the browser on their own desktop\n\nLooking at the browser tool description:\n- It says \"Browser automation\" - this is a headless browser on the server\n- There's mention of \"OpenClaw-managed browser\" vs \"user's browser\"\n- There's also mention of \"node\" target and \"host\" target\n\nThe issue is that the browser is running on the server (where OpenClaw is running), not on the user's local machine. So the user can't see it on their desktop.\n\nIf the user wants to see the browser on their local machine, I would need to either:\n1. Use a remote desktop solution\n2. Use the user's browser via the browser-automation skill with profile=\"user\"\n3. Use some other screen sharing/remote access method\n\nLet me check the browser skill to see if there's a way to use the user's local browser.\n\nActually, looking at the browser tool parameters:\n- `target`: \"sandbox|host|node\" \n- `profile`: \"user\" - \"For the logged-in user browser, use profile=\"user\"\"\n\nSo if I use `profile=\"user\"`, it might use the user's logged-in browser on their local machine. But that requires the user to have a browser running with OpenClaw's browser control server.\n\nActually wait - looking at the nodes skill and the openclaw-doctor skill, there might be a way to connect to the user's machine for remote control.\n\nBut for now, the user is saying they don't see any change on their desktop. \n\nThe headless browser on the server isn't visible to them, so I should explain this limitation and check if they have OpenClaw's remote browser control configured.","thinkingSignature":"3e4d46bb31221561faeee2f0858c7c022006cf152f7f346bc861180583508d41"},{"type":"text","text":"明白了！浏览器是在 **OpenClaw 运行的服务器上**打开的，不是你本地的桌面。所以你本地看不到变化。\n\n如果想让我控制**你本地的浏览器**，需要满足以下条件之一：\n\n1. **你的电脑上有配对的 OpenClaw Node**（手机/电脑配对功能）\n2. **你的浏览器运行了 OpenClaw 的远程控制端口**\n\n你的 OpenClaw 是装在哪里的？是本地电脑还是云端服务器？\n\n如果是你**本地电脑**上的 OpenClaw，理论上可以通过配对来控制你本地的浏览器。让我检查一下有没有已配对的节点：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_v6fhdji07v56_1","name":"nodes","arguments":{"action":"status"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":269,"output":603,"cacheRead":32929,"cacheWrite":55654,"totalTokens":89455,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779259745366,"responseId":"065c8c61e7e0514a8c87fc71837c11b2"}}
