{"type":"message","id":"d5774e2f","parentId":"84a08e9e","timestamp":"2026-05-20T06:49:39.590Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The nodes status shows an empty array - there are no paired nodes. This confirms that there are no devices paired with OpenClaw that could be used for remote browser control.\n\nSo the user's OpenClaw is running on a server (cloud), not on their local machine. The browser I opened is on that server, which is why the user can't see it on their desktop.\n\nI should explain this to the user and clarify that if they want browser control visible on their local machine, they would need to either:\n1. Run OpenClaw locally on their machine\n2. Set up some remote desktop solution\n3. Use screen sharing\n\nLet me explain the situation clearly.","thinkingSignature":"1b45a25d6dc0bb1fa5f8eb853e6682be988958126faf19cce4a13b4602af9d85"},{"type":"text","text":"没有配对的节点。这意味着 OpenClaw 运行在**云端服务器**上，不是你本地电脑。\n\n所以：\n- ✅ 我可以在服务器上打开浏览器（刚才已成功打开百度）\n- ❌ 但你本地桌面看不到（因为浏览器在云端服务器上）\n\n**解决方案：**\n\n如果你想让浏览器显示在你本地电脑上，需要：\n\n1. **本地安装 OpenClaw** 并配对 —— 这样我就能控制你本机的浏览器\n2. **远程桌面** —— 通过 RDP/VNC 等方式连接服务器查看\n3. **屏幕共享** —— 用其他远程控制软件\n\n你用的是云端服务器还是本地电脑跑 OpenClaw？如果是本地电脑，可以重新配对一下，这样我就能控制你本地的浏览器了。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":44108,"output":291,"cacheRead":45375,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":89774,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779259768011,"responseId":"065c8c7865c8030c3872664a0bcebaea"}}
