{"type":"message","id":"78c374fd","parentId":"88ea2abe","timestamp":"2026-05-20T06:50:55.254Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying they are using VNC (Virtual Network Computing) to connect to the server, so they can see the browser that I open on the server. They want me to continue operating the browser - they can see it through their VNC connection.\n\nSo now I can operate the browser freely and they will see the changes through VNC. Let me continue with the browser automation.\n\nThe user originally wanted me to open Baidu and they can see it via VNC. I already opened the browser and navigated to Baidu. Let me take a screenshot to confirm and then ask what they want me to do next - maybe they want me to search for something or interact with the page.\n\nActually, looking at the conversation flow:\n1. User asked me to open browser and visit www.baidu.com\n2. I did that, but initially the screenshot showed something else\n3. I re-navigated to baidu.com\n4. User said they couldn't see any changes (before they confirmed they use VNC)\n5. Now they're saying they use VNC and can see\n\nSo they should be able to see the browser with Baidu now via VNC. Let me take a fresh screenshot to confirm and then ask what they want to do.","thinkingSignature":"cc0709d13171eae68edd55d2fe31bf7968bff7533132c6d81ca20777ca3ebb04"},{"type":"text","text":"明白了！你通过 VNC 连接服务器，能看到我操作的浏览器。那我继续了。\n\n让我截个当前页面确认一下百度已经打开：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_az7cibtqeou4_1","name":"browser","arguments":{"action":"screenshot","targetId":"8F7138AA0DDEF8CF511945352639D66F"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":269,"output":335,"cacheRead":88354,"cacheWrite":1445,"totalTokens":90403,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779259843577,"responseId":"065c8cc3814c9a4c70da6d32ae0d2ec7"}}
