{"type":"message","id":"9abc1b89","parentId":"2247ba4d","timestamp":"2026-05-20T06:52:32.970Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the config doesn't have any explicit browser/cdp configuration. The browser tool in OpenClaw works through a browser control server. Let me check if there's a browser-related config section by looking at more of the file.\n\nActually, looking at the config, I see the `gateway` section and `plugins` section. The browser tool likely connects via WebSocket to the gateway's built-in browser control server.\n\nLet me check what the browser tool is trying to do. When I called `browser open`, it returned a `targetId` and `wsUrl` like `ws://127.0.0.1:18800/devtools/page/...`. This suggests the CDP (Chrome DevTools Protocol) is running on port 18800.\n\nBut the user said they can't see the browser on their VNC. This might mean:\n1. The browser is running in a headless mode\n2. The browser window isn't being displayed on the server's desktop that VNC is showing\n\nLet me check if there's a display issue - maybe the browser is running headless and not creating a visible window.\n\nLet me check what processes are running and what display is set.\n","thinkingSignature":"3815ddaebe45c7b63f199f6b831feab768d036fb9a6ee1f81cefd4e4990d9448"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_y1jcsxzdppdt_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"DISPLAY: $DISPLAY\" && ps aux | grep -i chrome | head -5 && ls /tmp/.X* 2>/dev/null || echo \"no X socket\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":81083,"output":300,"cacheRead":1152,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":82535,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779259935636,"responseId":"065c8d1f6bea1bd88d90f966fe6b38e4"}}
