{"type":"message","id":"bd8ec573","parentId":"2ee2be43","timestamp":"2026-05-20T06:53:40.647Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see the issue now! The Chrome is running with `--ozone-platform=headless` which means it's using headless mode (no display output). \n\nLooking at the Chrome process:\n- `--ozone-platform=headless` - this is headless mode\n- `--headless=new` - also headless\n- `--disable-gpu` - no GPU\n- `--ozone-override-screen-size=800,600` - overrides screen size to 800x600\n\nThe server has:\n- X server running on :1 (Display 1)\n- VNC server on port 5900\n- A user logged in via GNOME on :1\n\nSo the problem is that OpenClaw's browser is using headless Chrome, not a real display-attached Chrome. Headless Chrome doesn't render to any display - it only processes pages programmatically.\n\nIf the user wants to see the browser via VNC, I need to either:\n1. Use a non-headless Chrome that connects to the real X display (:1)\n2. Or use some other approach\n\nLooking at the openclaw.json config, I don't see any browser-specific configuration. The browser tool is using OpenClaw's built-in browser management which defaults to headless mode.\n\nTo fix this, we'd need to configure OpenClaw to use a non-headless Chrome with the real display. Let me check if there's a way to configure this.\n\nActually, looking at the docs path, there's a `browser-automation` skill. Let me read it to understand the browser configuration better.\n\nActually wait - the user might just want to see what's happening. Since they have VNC access to display :1, and the Chrome is headless, they won't see anything. The browser is running but not visible.\n\nThe solution is to start a Chrome that connects to the actual display :1 instead of running headless. But that's a configuration change that might affect how OpenClaw manages browsers.\n\nLet me just explain the situation clearly.\n","thinkingSignature":"2c3fabaf2019711d341281d96c8ce3b4a232fe01771f89752098a9af34df50c3"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n找到问题了！\n\n**问题原因：**\n\nChrome 启动时带了 `--headless=new` 和 `--ozone-platform=headless` 参数——这是**无头模式**，没有绑定到任何显示器，所以 VNC 看不到。\n\n服务器上有：\n- X display `:1`（你通过 VNC 看到的）\n- VNC 在 port 5900\n- 但 OpenClaw 的 Chrome 是 headless 模式，不渲染到任何显示\n\n**这就是为什么你 VNC 看不到百度——浏览器在后台 headless 跑着呢。**\n\n**要解决的话**，我需要重新打开一个 Chrome 连接到真实的 display `:1`，而不是 headless 模式。你要我试试吗？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":4731,"output":545,"cacheRead":79903,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":85179,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779259996265,"responseId":"065c8d5c4e9d2b64ef2c05b19778c4d5"}}
