{"type":"message","id":"e87ca569","parentId":"cf6f586b","timestamp":"2026-05-20T07:04:02.049Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to take over control of their current browser. They sent a message from Feishu (ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb is HALEI's open_id) with \"接管，我现在的浏览器\" meaning \"Take over, my current browser\".\n\nLooking at the conversation context, this is HALEI speaking from Feishu. They want me to control their current browser - not the headless Chrome on the server, but their local browser.\n\nBut wait - OpenClaw is running on a server (cloud), not on HALEI's local machine. So \"my current browser\" could mean:\n1. They want me to control the browser on the server (which is what we've been doing)\n2. They want to pair their local browser with OpenClaw\n\nLooking at the nodes status earlier - there were no paired nodes. So the user might be asking to pair their local browser with OpenClaw so they can see what I'm doing.\n\nActually, re-reading the conversation - earlier the user said they were using VNC to see the server, and the browser was headless. They also asked about tiktok shop and the browser was blocked.\n\nNow they're saying \"接管，我现在的浏览器\" - \"take over my current browser\". This might mean they want to start a NEW browser session that they can see, or they're asking if I can control their local browser on their own machine.\n\nGiven the context of the conversation - we've been trying to access TikTok Shop and the browser navigation was blocked. The user might want me to take over their LOCAL browser (not the server's headless Chrome) so they can see what's happening and potentially login.\n\nTo do this, I would need to either:\n1. Have OpenClaw running locally on their machine (which it doesn't - it's on the server)\n2. Use a browser that's connected to a display they can see\n\nThe simplest interpretation is: the user wants me to open a new browser window on the server that they can see via VNC (not headless), and control that.\n\nActually wait - the user is now speaking from Feishu. \n\nThe earlier \"你操作吧我能看到\" (you operate, I can see it) was from LeiChao via WeCom. Now HALEI via Feishu is saying \"接管，我现在的浏览器\" (take over my current browser). These appear to be two different people - LeiChao was using WeCom and could see via VNC, while HALEI is now speaking from Feishu.\n\nThe instruction to \"take over my current browser\" likely means HALEI wants me to control the browser on the server that they're connected to via VNC, not their local machine. If they're viewing the server through VNC, then \"my current browser\" would be the server's browser they're already watching through that connection.\n","thinkingSignature":"32913fe48823daec02c07db57b719941ca0368419fc2389a8d72cc1a0b58208d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_zo3b8midao5v_1","name":"browser","arguments":{"action":"status"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1936,"output":613,"cacheRead":86098,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":88647,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779260605862,"responseId":"065c8fc07939202a05da35a08f7d6922"}}
