{"type":"message","id":"79d769af","parentId":"53ba2d00","timestamp":"2026-05-20T07:05:07.984Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying \"不要用web_fetch 我用桌面的chrome\" - meaning \"don't use web_fetch, I'm using the desktop chrome\". \n\nThey're pointing out that I should not use web_fetch, and they have a desktop Chrome that they want me to use instead. \n\nBut wait - the browser I opened earlier was the headless Chrome that OpenClaw manages at port 18800. The user is saying they want me to use the desktop Chrome instead.\n\nBut looking at the system message, it's from Feishu DM from HALEI (ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb). This is a separate message from HALEI coming through the Feishu channel. Let me respond to this.\n\nThe user wants me to use their desktop Chrome. But I'm running on a server - I don't have direct access to their local machine's Chrome unless they're using some remote connection or have paired their machine.\n\nWait - looking at the nodes status earlier, it returned empty - no paired nodes. So I can't directly control a local browser on the user's machine.\n\nBut wait - the user is saying they're using desktop Chrome and they're connected via VNC to the server. Looking at the earlier commands:\n- DISPLAY is empty (not set)\n- X server is running on :1\n- VNC is active\n\nSo the user's VNC session is connected to display :1, and there's Chrome running there somewhere. But the Chrome that OpenClaw controls is the headless one at port 18800, not the desktop Chrome on display :1.\n\nLet me check if there's a way to control the desktop Chrome. Actually, Chrome has a remote debugging mode - if the user starts Chrome with `--remote-debugging-port=9222` on the same machine, I could potentially connect to it.\n\nBut the Chrome I'm controlling is at port 18800 (headless). The user wants me to control their desktop Chrome. For that to work, the user would need to:\n1. Start their desktop Chrome with remote debugging enabled\n2. OpenClaw would need to connect to that Chrome\n\nOr maybe the user has already started Chrome with remote debugging? Let me check if there's a Chrome running on another port.\n\n\nActually, there's only one Chrome running with debugging port 18800 (the headless one). The user is saying they want me to use their desktop Chrome instead, but the current setup only has the headless instance accessible.\n\nThe user explicitly said \"don't use web_fetch, I'm using desktop chrome\" - so they want me to operate their actual Chrome browser, not any web-based tool. Since they're connected via VNC, there's a desktop Chrome on display :1 that I could potentially control if Chrome had remote debugging enabled on a different port. But the system only shows the headless instance at 18800. I need to clarify with the user whether they can start their desktop Chrome with remote debugging enabled, or if there's another way to access it. The issue is that OpenClaw manages its own Chrome instance at port 18800, which is headless and separate from the desktop Chrome the user is running. To control their desktop browser, I'd need to either run OpenClaw locally on their machine or find a way to bridge to their existing Chrome instance—but given they're connected via VNC to a cloud server, the latter seems unlikely. Let me just ask them how they expect me to connect to their local Chrome when I'm running on a remote server.\n","thinkingSignature":"d9c05a380bca5bdc08c5f953a569c47fb1df760458519a7c8a7f7ab9d54a3c1f"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n明白了，你不让我用 web_fetch。\n\n但有个问题——我现在运行在**云端服务器**上，不是你本地电脑。我控制的 Chrome 是服务器上的 headless Chrome（端口 18800），不是你桌面上那个 Chrome。\n\n**你说的桌面 Chrome 是哪台机器上的？**\n\n如果是**服务器桌面**的 Chrome（在 VNC 能看到的 display :1 上），我需要你：\n\n1. 先确认服务器桌面 Chrome 是否开启了远程调试端口\n2. 或者告诉我怎么连接到那个 Chrome\n\n如果是**你自己电脑**的 Chrome，那我需要在你本地电脑上安装 OpenClaw 并配对，这样才能控制你本地的浏览器。\n\n你是想让我控制**哪台机器**上的 Chrome？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":