{"type":"message","id":"4ae8ed1f","parentId":"0f966d34","timestamp":"2026-05-20T07:06:18.214Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying \"和你在一个服务器上\" - meaning \"on the same server as you\". So the user is on the same cloud server where OpenClaw is running, and they want me to control the Chrome on that server that they can see through VNC.\n\nThe issue is that OpenClaw's browser tool is configured to use its own Chrome instance (headless) at port 18800, not the desktop Chrome that's visible on the VNC display.\n\nTo control the desktop Chrome that the user sees through VNC, I would need to either:\n1. Connect to that Chrome's remote debugging interface (if it's running with `--remote-debugging-port`)\n2. Or restart Chrome on the server with remote debugging enabled and without headless mode\n\nBut looking at the browser status, it shows:\n- `headless: true`\n- `headlessSource: \"linux-display-fallback\"`\n- `color: \"#FF4500\"` (this might be an indicator of which display)\n\nActually, looking at the `headlessSource: \"linux-display-fallback\"` - this suggests that OpenClaw detected the headless mode is using a Linux display fallback. Maybe the Chrome is actually running on a virtual display?\n\nWait, the user is on the same server and uses VNC. If Chrome is running headless on the server, the user won't see it. But if Chrome is running on the real display (:1), the user would see it via VNC.\n\nI think the user wants me to take control of their Chrome that's visible on the VNC display. But for that to work, I need to know if their Chrome is running with remote debugging enabled, or if I need to restart Chrome in a way that connects to the real display.\n\nLet me check if there's another Chrome instance running or if the user's Chrome has remote debugging enabled. I could try to connect to common Chrome debugging ports like 9222 (the default).\n\nActually, I should ask the user to check if their Chrome is running with remote debugging, or I could try to scan for Chrome instances with debugging ports.\n\n\nI could also attempt using the browser tool with `profile=\"user\"` to see if OpenClaw has a way to connect to the user's existing Chrome instance.","thinkingSignature":"4ee31c73e7bd69145fc0f12066220392df4d262dae4fa0e2c0965f8ac7f4bfcf"},{"type":"text","text":"明白了！你和我都在同一台云端服务器上，你想让我控制 VNC 能看到的那个桌面 Chrome。\n\n问题是 OpenClaw 现在控制的是**另一个 headless Chrome**（端口 18800），不是你 VNC 看到桌面上那个 Chrome。\n\n让我看看能不能连接到你的桌面 Chrome。你的 Chrome 开启远程调试了吗？比如启动时加了 `--remote-debugging-port=9222`？\n\n或者，让我试试直接连接到你桌面的 Chrome：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_psey3giej5qo_1","name":"browser","arguments":{"action":"status","target":"host","profile":"user"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":269,"output":590,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":103341,"totalTokens":104200,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779260754279,"responseId":"065c9052906cfda92b16a38388678579"}}
