{"type":"message","id":"5f01f828","parentId":"964a7b38","timestamp":"2026-05-20T07:06:46.490Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The browser tool with profile=\"user\" and target=\"host\" timed out. This means there's no user Chrome available to attach to, or the Chrome MCP server isn't running for the user's browser.\n\nLet me think about what's happening:\n1. The user's Chrome on the server is running on display :1 (VNC session)\n2. OpenClaw's browser tool uses its own headless Chrome at port 18800\n3. When I tried profile=\"user\", it timed out trying to connect to the user's Chrome MCP\n\nThe issue is that the user's Chrome is running in a VNC session on display :1, but it's not running with remote debugging enabled, and there's no Chrome MCP server running for the user's browser.\n\nFor me to control the user's visible Chrome, I would need:\n1. The user to start Chrome with `--remote-debugging-port=9222` (or some port)\n2. Then I could try to connect to it\n\nBut wait - looking at the browser skill again, there might be a way to use CDP directly to connect to a remote Chrome instance. But that requires knowing the CDP websocket URL.\n\nActually, let me just explain the situation to the user. The headless Chrome I have access to is different from the desktop Chrome they see via VNC. To control the desktop Chrome, they would need to start it with remote debugging enabled.\n\nBut actually - thinking more about this - maybe the user is asking me to take control of the CURRENT browser session (the headless one I already have open), not the desktop one. But they said \"我用桌面的chrome\" (I'm using desktop chrome), which suggests they want me to use the desktop one.\n\nLet me explain the limitation and suggest a solution - starting Chrome with remote debugging on the server so I can control the desktop Chrome.","thinkingSignature":"04d7c1c4b349dd6376ba3d496625364c2d0495bb1c24986e55d36c3cd366c656"},{"type":"text","text":"尝试连接失败了。原因是：\n\n你的桌面 Chrome 运行在 VNC 的 display :1 上，但 Chrome 没有开启远程调试模式，所以 OpenClaw 无法连接。\n\n**解决方案：**\n\n你的桌面 Chrome 需要开启远程调试，我才能控制。操作步骤：\n\n1. **关闭你现在的 Chrome**\n\n2. **用命令行重新启动 Chrome，开启调试模式：**\n```bash\ngoogle-chrome --remote-debugging-port=9222 --display=:1\n```\n\n或者如果你用的是完整路径：\n```bash\n/usr/bin/google-chrome --remote-debugging-port=9222 --display=:1\n```\n\n3. **启动后告诉我**，我就能连接到你那个桌面 Chrome 了\n\n这样 Chrome 既保持可视化的桌面模式，又能被我通过 CDP 远程控制。\n\n你能按这个步骤操作一下吗？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":59053,"output":529,"cacheRead":45196,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":104778,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779260787991,"responseId":"065c9074ac21f46c589663e5fdbc405c"}}
