{"type":"message","id":"23200930","parentId":"80e7f69f","timestamp":"2026-05-20T07:12:05.813Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying in the system settings there's a technical section with a \"browser\" setting that's not started. This is referring to the OpenClaw's browser MCP or browser service that needs to be running.\n\nLet me check if there's a browser service that needs to be started. Looking at the earlier browser status, it said \"MCP\" in the error message about \"Chrome MCP existing-session attach for profile user timed out\". This suggests there's a Chrome MCP server that needs to be running.\n\nLet me try to check what browser-related services or settings exist. The user might be referring to some kind of browser bridge or CDP bridge that needs to be enabled.\n\nActually, let me just ask the user what exactly they're seeing - which settings they're referring to. Or maybe I can help start the browser service.\n\nWait - looking at the nodes tool earlier, there were no paired nodes. The user might be referring to some kind of node/browser pairing setting.\n\nActually, I think the user is talking about the OpenClaw desktop app settings - maybe in the Tauri desktop app there's a \"browser\" setting that's not started. The \"browser MCP\" might refer to the browser control service.\n\nLet me try to understand what the user is saying. They're in the system settings and there's a \"browser\" option under \"technical settings\" that's not started. This sounds like they're referring to the OpenClaw desktop application (Tauri) settings.\n\nLet me check the browser-automation skill to see what browser-related services exist and how to start them.\n\nActually, maybe I should just ask the user to clarify what exactly they're referring to, or ask them to show me a screenshot of what they're seeing.\n","thinkingSignature":"8b3f759769d0dabf630dfd748b457855eafd54e90435b40979fc39c232682936"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n你