{"type":"message","id":"de0a1190","parentId":"27678ac7","timestamp":"2026-05-20T07:43:14.316Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[media attached: media://inbound/1f26d237-51b8-4706-aaf3-9a7910182247.jpg (image/jpeg) | media://inbound/1f26d237-51b8-4706-aaf3-9a7910182247.jpg]\nTo send an image back, prefer the message tool (media/path/filePath). If you must inline, use MEDIA:https://example.com/image.jpg (spaces ok, quote if needed) or a safe relative path like MEDIA:./image.jpg. Absolute and ~ paths only work when they stay inside your allowed file-read boundary; host file:// URLs are blocked. Keep caption in the text body.\nSystem: [2026-05-20 15:42:32 GMT+8] Feishu[default] DM | ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb [msg:om_x100b6fe210acd8bcc3a2d645263ded7, post, 1 attachment(s)]\n\n[Image]\nUser text:\n[Feishu ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb Wed 2026-05-20 15:42 GMT+8] ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb: /home/halei/.openclaw/media/inbound/1f26d237-51b8-4706-aaf3-9a7910182247.jpg\n以后就像这样\nDescription:\nThe image shows a screenshot of a code editor, likely Visual Studio Code, displaying a JSON configuration file. The code defines a `\"browser\"` object with a `\"defaultProfile\": \"user\"` and a `\"profiles\"` object containing two entries: `\"work\"` and `\"personal\"`. Each profile has a `\"cdpPort\"` (18801 and 18802) and a hex `\"color\"` code.\n\nThe editor has a dark theme with syntax highlighting. A portion of the `profiles` object is highlighted. A small loading circle and the Chinese text \"正在缓冲...\" (Bu"}],"timestamp":1779262979366}}
{"type":"message","id":"718bc2e2","parentId":"de0a1190","timestamp":"2026-05-20T07:43:46.834Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is showing me a screenshot of a configuration file in VS Code. It shows:\n\n```json\n\"browser\": {\n  \"defaultProfile\": \"user\",\n  \"profiles\": {\n    \"work\": {\n      \"cdpPort\": 18801,\n      \"color\": \"#... (something)\"\n    },\n    \"personal\": {\n      \"cdpPort\": 18802,\n      \"color\": \"#... (something)\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThe user said \"以后就像这样\" which means \"from now on it will be like this\" - they're showing me the format for creating separate browser profile configurations.\n\nThey want me to create browser profiles in the openclaw.json config file. Looking at the schema from earlier, I can see there's a `browser.profiles` configuration option that allows defining named browser profile connection maps.\n\nThe user wants:\n- `defaultProfile: \"user\"` - probably using the existing Chrome at port 18800\n- `profiles` with multiple named profiles (work, personal) each with their own `cdpPort`\n\nBut wait - I need to understand the architecture better. They have Chrome instances at different ports. The current Chrome is at port 18800 (managed by OpenClaw's headless Chrome).\n\nThe user wants to create profiles like \"work\" and \"personal\" that point to different Chrome instances at different CDP ports (18801, 18802).\n\nBut for this to work, the user needs to have Chrome instances running at those ports first. These would be manually started Chrome instances with remote debugging enabled.\n\nThe user is showing me the target configuration format. I should help them apply this configuration.\n\nBut actually, let me think about what the user wants:\n1. They want multiple Chrome instances running on different ports (for different purposes/profiles)\n2. They want OpenClaw to be able to use these different Chrome instances via browser profiles\n3. The default profile \"user\" would use the Chrome at port 18800 (or whatever port the current headless Chrome is on)\n\n\n4. For the configuration to work, they need to manually start separate Chrome instances with remote debugging enabled on ports 18801 and 18802, then I can configure OpenClaw to route to these different profiles based on their needs.\n","thinkingSignature":"3a3832aeae30344d31cb0044a17ce5785fd843d44f4e6c334ea4e6f871cde0e7"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n看到了！你这是在配置**多浏览器独立模式**：\n\n```json\n\"browser\": {\n  \"defaultProfile\": \"user\",\n  \"profiles\": {\n    \"work\": {\n      \"cdpPort\": 18801,\n      \"color\": \"#... (颜色)\"\n    },\n    \"personal\": {\n      \"cdpPort\": 18802,\n      \"color\": \"#... (颜色)\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**你这是要在服务器上同时跑多个 Chrome 实例**，每个用不同端口（18801、18802），分别做不同用途（工作、个人）。\n\n**前提条件：**\n这些 Chrome 实例需要你先手动启动，并开启远程调试。例如：\n\n```bash\n# Chrome 1 (work) - display :1\ngoogle-chrome --remote-debugging-port=18801 --display=:1\n\n# Chrome 2 (personal) - display :2  \ngoogle-chrome --remote-debugging-port=18802 --display=:2\n```\n\n**你想现在就让这些 Chrome 跑起来吗？**\n\n告诉我：\n1. 你是想用 VNC 桌面上已经开着的 Chrome 吗？（display :1）\n2. 还是想让我帮你启动新的 Chrome 实例？\n\n这样我才能正确配置 `cdpUrl` 指向对应的端口。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":7756,"output":724,"cacheRead":87673,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":96153,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779262994435,"responseId":"065c99127cc50a7083d9a69a76884b91"}}
{"type":"message","id":"73a56836","parentId":"718bc2e2","timestamp":"2026-05-20T07:44:40.062Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"chat_id\": \"user:ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b6fe22b204490c31cf80e68ce8b6\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Wed 2026-05-20 15:44 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\"\n}\n```\n\n你不是独立模式吗，为啥还要开浏览器调试模，"}],"timestamp":1779263079946}}
{"type":"custom_message","customType":"openclaw.runtime-context","content":"System: [2026-05-20 15:44:31 GMT+8] Feishu[kiit] DM | ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb [msg:om_x100b6fe22b204490c31cf80e68ce8b6]","display":false,"details":{"source":"openclaw-runtime-context"},"id":"13bd6b8e","parentId":"73a56836","timestamp":"2026-05-20T07:44:40.136Z"}
{"type":"message","id":"212f2b6f","parentId":"13bd6b8e","timestamp":"2026-05-20T07:45:19.607Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is pointing out that I should be using \"独立模式\" (standalone mode) for the browser, and questioning why I need to enable browser debugging mode.\n\nLooking at the browser schema again, there's a `browser.headless` option that can be set to `false` to make the browser non-headless (visible). And there's also `attachOnly` mode.\n\nThe user is saying that since OpenClaw is running on the server and they have a VNC desktop, they should be able to just use the display directly without needing remote debugging ports.\n\nActually, looking at the earlier browser status:\n```\n\"headless\": true,\n\"headlessSource\": \"linux-display-fallback\",\n```\n\nThis suggests that OpenClaw detected there was no display available and fell back to headless mode. But now the user has a VNC session with display :1. So if we configure the browser properly, it should be able to use that display.\n\nLet me check the browser configuration more carefully. The issue is that the Chrome was started with `--ozone-platform=headless` which forces headless mode regardless of the display setting.\n\nFor a truly \"独立模式\" (standalone mode) browser that connects to the actual desktop display, we would need:\n1. `headless: false` in the config\n2. The Chrome to be started without `--ozone-platform=headless`\n3. A proper DISPLAY environment variable pointing to :1\n\nBut actually, looking at the schema, there might be a way to configure the browser to NOT be headless and use the existing display.\n\nLet me think about what the user is asking. They're saying:\n- \"你不是独立模式吗\" - \"Aren't you running in standalone mode?\"\n- \"为啥还要开浏览器调试模\" - \"Why do you still need to enable browser debugging mode?\"\n\nI think the user is confused about the terminology. \"独立模式\" in the browser context might mean \"managed by OpenClaw\" vs \"external browser\". \n\nLooking at the browser schema, `attachOnly: true` would restrict the browser to attach-only behavior without starting local browser processes. But the issue we had was that OpenClaw WAS starting its own Chrome, but it was starting in headless mode because of how it was configured/detected.\n\nThe user might be asking: if OpenClaw's browser is in \"独立模式\" (standalone/independent mode), why can't it just use the display directly without needing remote debugging? For OpenClaw to control a browser on the display, it needs either a remote debugging port or direct access to the display—remote debugging is the standard Chrome DevTools Protocol approach, but if OpenClaw is truly managing its own Chrome instance in standalone mode, it should be able to start it with display access rather than requiring separate debugging setup. so Chrome could use it)\n3. OR use `browser.attachOnly: false` and let OpenClaw manage the browser with proper display settings\n\nThe `attachOnly` option is key here - when disabled, OpenClaw can launch its own browser instances rather than just attaching to existing ones. I need to check if there are extra arguments being passed to Chrome that force headless mode, and disable that. I should apply the simpler configuration the user is showing me: `headless: false`, `defaultProfile: \"user\"`, and the profiles with different cdpPorts for managing separate Chrome instances.\n","thinkingSignature":"02d336b867449309d4900d96c6fb1fe22e0f90870539b759f92907491e4ba675"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n你说得对！我理解错了。\n\n独立模式（managed browser）就是 OpenClaw 自己启动并管理 Chrome，不需要外部调试端口。\n\n问题在于：OpenClaw 的 Chrome 被启动成了 `--ozone-platform=headless`（强制无头），而不是连接到 VNC 的桌面 display。\n\n**配置独立模式很简单：**\n\n```json\n\"browser\": {\n  \"headless\": false,\n  \"defaultProfile\": \"user\",\n  \"profiles\": {\n    \"work\": {\n      \"cdpPort\": 18801,\n      \"color\": \"#3B82F6\"\n    },\n    \"personal\": {\n      \"cdpPort\": 18802,\n      \"color\": \"#10B981\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n关键就是 `headless: false` —— 告诉 OpenClaw 启动**可视化** Chrome 而不是无头模式。\n\n**但是**，之前 Chrome 被强制变成 headless 是因为检测不到 display（`DISPLAY` 环境变量为空，X server 在 :1 而不是默认的 :0）。\n\n要让可视化 Chrome 显示在你的 VNC 桌面上，还需要：\n- `DISPLAY=:1` 或者\n- 在 `extraArgs` 里加 `--display=:1`\n\n我现在就把配置改成 `headless: false`，然后重启 Gateway。这样下次打开的 Chrome 应该就能在 VNC 桌面上看到了。\n\n要我现在执行吗？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":10697,"output":979,"cacheRead":86077,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":97753,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779263080423,"responseId":"065c9969eb7c6ceb1b83ab44c66cd783"}}
{"type":"message","id":"397cc00c","parentId":"212f2b6f","timestamp":"2026-05-20T07:46:06.729Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"chat_id\": \"user:ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b6fe2259b40a0c37ca6c6709778c\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Wed 2026-05-20 15:45 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\"\n}\n```\n\n执行，把，我vnc能看到"}],"timestamp":1779263166613}}
