{"type":"message","id":"fad2e126","parentId":"44c7b4ca","timestamp":"2026-05-20T07:48:41.068Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The browser status shows:\n- `headless: false` - good, headless mode is now disabled\n- `running: false` - no browser is currently running\n- `cdpReady: false` - CDP not ready\n- `profile: \"openclaw\"` - using the openclaw profile\n\nNow the user wants me to open TWO browsers - one for \"work\" profile访问百度 and one for \"personal\" profile访问QQ.\n\nBut wait - I only set up the profiles in the config, I didn't actually create the Chrome instances at those ports. The profiles reference cdpPort 18801 and 18802, but those Chrome instances don't exist yet.\n\nLet me try to start the work profile browser first and navigate to Baidu, then start the personal profile browser and navigate to QQ.\n\nActually, let me try opening two browsers with different profiles. I'll use the `browser` tool with different profile settings.\n\nBut wait - the browser tool has a `profile` parameter. Let me try opening a browser with profile=\"work\" to see if it works. If the Chrome instance at port 18801 doesn't exist, it might fail or it might start a new one.\n\nActually, I think I need to understand the flow better:\n1. With `attachOnly: false`, OpenClaw can start its own browser instances\n2. The `profiles` configuration tells OpenClaw which CDP port to use for each profile\n3. If a Chrome is already running at that port, it attaches to it; otherwise it starts a new one\n\nLet me try opening the work browser first.\n","thinkingSignature":"c6c62e9ea2846a7094136a3b6e1e64f30c6aceac151a7d62e0dadbf5cdec2490"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_emcsqqp68wue_1","name":"browser","arguments":{"action":"open","profile":"work","url":"https://www.baidu.com"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":7853,"output":375,"cacheRead":90792,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":99020,"cost":{"input":0,