{"type":"message","id":"7cbaf635","parentId":"ca954315","timestamp":"2026-05-20T07:49:18.953Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The browser config only shows `headless: false`, not the profiles we tried to set. It seems the config patch failed earlier (because those paths are protected), and the CLI command `openclaw config set` only set `headless: false`, not the profiles.\n\nLet me check what the current openclaw.json has for the browser section, and then figure out how to properly add the profiles. The user wants:\n- work profile with cdpPort 18801\n- personal profile with cdpPort 18802\n\nBut those paths were protected when I tried to patch. Let me try a different approach - maybe I can edit the openclaw.json file directly, or try adding the profiles one at a time.\n\nActually, looking at the error message earlier: \"gateway config.patch cannot change protected config paths: browser.defaultProfile, browser.headless, browser.profiles.personal.cdpPort, browser.profiles.personal.color, browser.profiles.work.cdpPort, browser.profiles.work.color\"\n\nThese specific paths are protected. But maybe I can set the profiles differently, or use the raw file edit approach.\n\nWait - the user is asking me to open two browsers. The issue is:\n1. The profiles aren't configured yet (because the patch failed)\n2. Even if they were, the Chrome instances at ports 18801 and 18802 don't exist yet\n\nThe user wants me to open:\n- \"work\" profile browser → go to baidu.com\n- \"personal\" profile browser → go to qq.com\n\nBut the profiles don't exist in the config yet. And the Chrome instances at the CDP ports don't exist either.\n\nLet me think about this differently. The user has VNC and can see the desktop. They want to open TWO separate Chrome windows on the VNC desktop. But:\n1. For that to work, I need to be able to start Chrome instances on specific displays/ports\n2. The profiles need to be configured in OpenClaw first\n\nLet me try a different approach - let me just try to open a browser with the \"user\" profile (which is the default) and see if it works now that headless is false. If that works, maybe I can open multiple tabs instead of multiple profiles.\n\n\nSince the profiles are protected and the Chrome instances don't exist yet, maybe I should first test if the headless: false setting actually works by opening a single browser with the default profile to check if it appears on VNC. Then I can figure out how to handle the multiple browser scenario.\n","thinkingSignature":"f99445c1c81b4cca9388e1bcb9ae388a5b0cbd82bbd8d1c5bb00dec39813a24e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_aru9r0obarrr_1","name":"browser","arguments":{"action":"open","profile":"user","url":"https://www.baidu.com"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":4626,"output":564,"cacheRead":94177,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":99367,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779263334448,"responseId":"065c9a66e3835ebbdaedd9f84ef708bc"}}
