{"type":"message","id":"0ba2b598","parentId":"8a6e42af","timestamp":"2026-05-20T07:50:30.373Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The browser opened successfully and I can see Baidu in the screenshot! The browser is now visible (not headless) since the user should be able to see it on VNC. The headless setting is now false.\n\nNow I need to:\n1. Open a second browser (profile \"personal\") pointing to QQ.com\n2. But the profile \"personal\" doesn't exist yet\n\nThe user asked me to:\n1. Open one browser for Baidu (which I just did)\n2. Open another browser for QQ\n\nBut the profiles \"work\" and \"personal\" I tried to configure earlier were blocked due to protected config paths. The only profile available are \"openclaw\" and \"user\".\n\nLet me try to open a second browser instance directly - maybe I can just open another tab or window for QQ. Let me try with a new tab first, or try to use the existing browser with a different approach.\n\nActually, looking at the browser status - it says \"running: true\" now after I opened the first page. Maybe I can just navigate the existing browser to qq.com for the second one, but that would replace baidu.\n\nWhat I should do is try to open a NEW browser instance - but that might require using a different profile or a different approach. \n\nLet me try to just use the browser tool to open QQ in a new tab or new window - but the browser tool doesn't seem to have a \"newWindow\" option based on what I saw earlier.\n\nActually, looking at the available browser actions - there's no explicit \"newWindow\" or \"newTab\" action. The \"open\" action opened a new page in the existing browser. So maybe I need to configure the profiles first before I can have multiple browsers.\n\nLet me explain to the user what happened and ask about the profile configuration that failed earlier.Actually wait - the profiles configuration I tried to set was blocked due to protected config paths. Let me check what config paths are protected and see if I can set them individually.\n\nActually, I should tell the user the situation:1. Baidu is now open ✅\n2. For QQ and multiple profiles, I need to configure the profiles properly first, which requires addressing the protected config paths issue.\n\nLet me send the screenshot of Baidu and explain that I need to properly configure the multi-profile setup first.\n","thinkingSignature":"e9c9cfb9e9d2cef2b80c019b0f0e6993fef2698e054f488bfaf89926a619bb72"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n百度的浏览器已经打开了，你能在 VNC 上看到吗？\n\n![百度](tool-image.png)\n\n---\n\n但是有个问题：**多浏览器配置被阻止了**\n\n刚才我想配置 `browser.profiles.work` 和 `browser.profiles.personal`，但系统说这些是**受保护的配置路径**，不允许修改：\n\n```\ncannot change protected config paths: \nbrowser.defaultProfile, browser.headless, browser.profiles.personal.cdpPort, \nbrowser.profiles.personal.color, browser.profiles.work.cdpPort, browser.profiles.work.color\n```\n\n所以现在只能打开**一个**浏览器实例，没法同时开两个独立配置的浏览器。\n\n**要开多个浏览器，需要：**\n\n1. 先手动启动多个 Chrome 实例（不同端口）\n2. 然后通过 `browser.profiles` 指向它们\n\n你想让我先试试同时开两个标签页（百度和 QQ 在同一个浏览器里），还是先把多浏览器配置搞定了再说？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":4652,"output":665,"cacheRead":94544,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":99861,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779263396690,"responseId":"065c9aa577af36f18332485e78bf2906"}}
