{"type":"message","id":"5efd6889","parentId":"753bf8d0","timestamp":"2026-05-20T07:51:01.948Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying \"接管呢\" - they're asking me to take over/controlling the browser, and they mention they can click \"通过\" (approve/pass) on their end. This sounds like they're referring to the pairing/approval flow for connecting to their browser.\n\nEarlier when I tried to use profile=\"user\", I got an error:\n\"Chrome MCP existing-session attach failed for profile \\\"user\\\". Make sure Google Chrome's default profile is running locally with remote debugging enabled.\"\n\nThe user is saying they can click \"通过\" (approve) - this suggests there's an approval/pairing flow for the browser connection. \n\nIn the OpenClaw context, this might be referring to the browser pairing/approval system. When I try to connect to a browser profile that requires approval, the user can approve it on their end.\n\nLet me try the browser tool again with profile=\"user\" and see if there's an approval flow.\n","thinkingSignature":"ea294b6b324be027998dd86cda7fdb2e0c8cbe35e3c4407b7194284758749b29"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_j4bv4yj51ifa_1","name":"browser","arguments":{"action":"open","profile":"user","url":"https://www.qq.com"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":6326,"output":237,"cacheRead":93553,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":100116,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779263444446,"responseId":"065c9ada6025b457641fdf7d2d6f79c3"}}
