{"type":"message","id":"65fdd442","parentId":"58b0c54b","timestamp":"2026-05-20T07:51:18.456Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user profile requires Chrome MCP running with remote debugging enabled. But the user is saying \"接管呢\" (take over/take control) - they might be offering to approve or click through something.\n\nActually looking at the error, it says \"Chrome MCP existing-session attach failed\" - this is trying to connect to an EXISTING Chrome session with remote debugging. The user said they can click to approve, so maybe they need to approve the MCP connection.\n\nLet me try to use profile=\"user\" but the issue is Chrome MCP isn't running. Let me try the attach action explicitly and see if it triggers an approval on the user's side.\n\nActually, maybe I should try `browser action=start` for profile=\"user\" to start a new Chrome instance with remote debugging enabled?\n","thinkingSignature":"956c8eaa24525a53273cebbedae5ae2aa2054eb7b9925ae432b54301ed702d10"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_af7bub63pc9i_1","name":"browser","arguments":{"action":"start","profile":"user"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":4725,"output":192,"cacheRead":95275,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":100192,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779263466296,"responseId":"065c9aeaae9dc1ded0f44086d07602d6"}}
